{
  "One-Sided Limits": "",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "",
  "What is lim(xвҶ’0вҒә) 1/x?": "",
  "As x approaches 0 from the right (positive values), 1/x grows without bound toward +вҲһ.": "",
  "What is lim(xвҶ’0вҒ») 1/x?": "",
  "As x approaches 0 from the left (negative values), 1/x decreases without bound toward вҲ’вҲһ.": "",
  "If f(x) = {x+1, x<2; 5, xвүҘ2}, what is lim(xвҶ’2вҒ») f(x)?": "",
  "For x < 2, f(x) = x + 1. As x вҶ’ 2вҒ»: 2 + 1 = 3.": "",
  "Using the same function from Q4, what is lim(xвҶ’2вҒә) f(x)?": "",
  "For x вүҘ 2, f(x) = 5. As x вҶ’ 2вҒә: f(x) = 5.": "",
  "What is lim(xвҶ’3вҒә) вҲҡ(x вҲ’ 3)?": "",
  "As x вҶ’ 3вҒә, x вҲ’ 3 вҶ’ 0вҒә, so вҲҡ(x вҲ’ 3) вҶ’ 0.": "",
  "What is lim(xвҶ’3вҒ») вҲҡ(x вҲ’ 3)?": "",
  "For x < 3, x вҲ’ 3 is negative, so вҲҡ(x вҲ’ 3) is not real. The left-hand limit does not exist in the real numbers.": "",
  "If f(x) = |x вҲ’ 1|/(x вҲ’ 1), what is lim(xвҶ’1вҒә) f(x)?": "",
  "For x > 1, |xвҲ’1| = xвҲ’1, so f(x) = (xвҲ’1)/(xвҲ’1) = 1.": "",
  "What is lim(xвҶ’1вҒ») |x вҲ’ 1|/(x вҲ’ 1)?": "",
  "For x < 1, |xвҲ’1| = вҲ’(xвҲ’1), so f(x) = вҲ’(xвҲ’1)/(xвҲ’1) = вҲ’1.": "",
  "What is a 'one-sided limit'?": "",
  "A one-sided limit examines the behavior of f(x) as x approaches a from one side only: left (x вҶ’ aвҒ») or right (x вҶ’ aвҒә).": "",
  "What is a 'jump discontinuity'?": "",
  "A jump discontinuity occurs when lim(xвҶ’aвҒ») f(x) and lim(xвҶ’aвҒә) f(x) both exist but are different values.": "",
  "What is a 'left-hand limit'?": "",
  "The left-hand limit, written lim(xвҶ’aвҒ») f(x), is the value f(x) approaches when x comes from the left (x < a).": "",
  "What is a 'right-hand limit'?": "",
  "The right-hand limit, written lim(xвҶ’aвҒә) f(x), is the value f(x) approaches when x comes from the right (x > a).": "",
  "What is the 'greatest integer function' (floor function)?": "",
  "The floor function вҢҠxвҢӢ rounds down to the nearest integer. For example, вҢҠ3.7вҢӢ = 3 and вҢҠвҲ’1.2вҢӢ = вҲ’2.": "",
  "A parking garage charges $5 for the first hour and $3 for each additional hour (or part thereof). The cost function has jump discontinuities. What is lim(tвҶ’2вҒ») C(t)?": "",
  "For t just under 2 hours, the charge is $5 + $3 = $8 (first hour plus one additional hour).": "",
  "A tax bracket system charges 10% on income up to $10,000 and 20% on income above $10,000. The marginal rate function r(x) = {0.10 if x вүӨ 10000; 0.20 if x > 10000}. What is lim(xвҶ’10000вҒә) r(x)?": "",
  "For x just above $10,000, the rate is 0.20. So lim(xвҶ’10000вҒә) r(x) = 0.20.": "",
  "A dose of medication is modeled by D(t) = {100 if t < 6; 200 if t вүҘ 6} mg, where a second dose is given at t = 6 hours. What is lim(tвҶ’6вҒ») D(t)?": "",
  "Just before the second dose at t = 6, D(t) = 100 mg.": "",
  "A shipping company charges by weight: $5 for 0 < w вүӨ 1 lb, $8 for 1 < w вүӨ 3 lb, and $12 for 3 < w вүӨ 5 lb. What is lim(wвҶ’1вҒә) C(w)?": "",
  "For w just above 1 lb, the cost switches to $8.": "",
  "An electrical circuit switches on at t = 0. The current is I(t) = {0, t < 0; 5, t вүҘ 0} amps. What is lim(tвҶ’0вҒ») I(t)?": "",
  "Before the switch at t = 0, I(t) = 0. So lim(tвҶ’0вҒ») I(t) = 0.": "",
  "A utility company charges $0.10/kWh for the first 500 kWh and $0.15/kWh after that. At exactly 500 kWh, what is lim(xвҶ’500вҒә) of the marginal rate?": "",
  "For usage just above 500 kWh, the marginal rate is $0.15/kWh.": "",
  "A roller coaster's speed at the bottom of a loop is modeled by v(t) = {8t if t < 5; 40 if t = 5; вҲ’8(tвҲ’10) if t > 5}. What is lim(tвҶ’5вҒ») v(t) and lim(tвҶ’5вҒә) v(t)?": "",
  "lim(tвҶ’5вҒ») = 8(5) = 40. lim(tвҶ’5вҒә) = вҲ’8(5вҲ’10) = вҲ’8(вҲ’5) = 40. Both one-sided limits equal 40.": ""
}